A
> USB stick you purchase from a store is safer than one given to you by
> someone
> you don=92t know =97 or one you find in a parking lot.
>
> 8. For file transfer, a writable optical disk (CD or DVD) is safer than a
> USB
> stick. Malware can silently write data to a USB stick, but it can=92t spi=
n
> the
