br>
Tails from a read-only DVD =97 you can keep your data on an encrypted USB s=
tick<br>
=97 is even more secure. Of course, this is not foolproof, but it greatly<b=
r>
reduces the potential avenues for attack.<br>
<br>
Yes, all this is advice for the paranoid. And it=92s probably impossible to=
<br>
enforce for any network more complicated than a single computer with a sing=
le<br>
user. But if you=92re thinking about setting up an air-gapped computer, you=
<br>
already believe that some very powerful attackers are after you personally.=
